Classes
Class
Description
Main
This Main class is where the Main Menu class and its functions are used.
MainMenu
This class is where a operator, manager, or provider is directed to their terminal.
Manager
The Manager class illustrates how the manager interacts with the manager terminal.
ManagerTerminal
This represents the terminal where managers can login and request reports.
MemberList
This class holds member data used for member reports.
Operator
The Operator class illustrates how the operator interacts with the operator terminal.
OperatorTerminal
This class calls the update member and provider classes so the operator can perform different tasks.
Provider
The Provider class illustrates how the provider interacts with the provider terminal.
ProviderController
This performs all the actions that a Provider can do.
ProviderDirectory
Holds all service codes, names, and prices.
ProviderList
Generates a provider list with each providers information.
ProviderTerminal
This class calls the methods within the ProviderController so the provider can perform certain actions.
ReportController
Performs all the actions of the manager and runs the main accounting procedure.
ServiceList
Creates a service list containing comments and dates of services.
UpdateMember
Performs the actions of adding, deleting, and updating members.
UpdateProvider
Performs the actions of adding, deleting, and updating providers.
